	voiceHeading={`Bible verses for veterans: the Father's voice`}
	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for veterans in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your faithful Father, straight to what you carry. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Deuteronomy 31:6`, slug: `deuteronomy`, ch: 31, text: `Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid, for your Father goes with you; He will never leave you nor forsake you.`, note: `The Father who went with you into every deployment has not left your side now that you're home.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 34:18`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 34, text: `Your Father is close to the brokenhearted, and He saves those whose spirit is crushed.`, note: `When the grief and the weight feel like too much, your Father draws nearest — not farthest.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 41:10`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 41, text: `Do not fear, for I am with you; do not be dismayed, for I am your Father. I will strengthen you, I will help you, I will uphold you with My righteous right hand.`, note: `On the nights you feel you have nothing left, your Father is the one holding you up.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 147:3`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 147, text: `Your Father heals the brokenhearted and binds up every one of their wounds.`, note: `The wounds no one can see — the ones you don't talk about — your Father tends to with His own hands.` },
		{ ref: `Joshua 1:9`, slug: `joshua`, ch: 1, text: `Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid, for your Father is with you wherever you go.`, note: `Wherever the transition takes you, you do not go alone — your Father goes with you.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 23:4`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `Even when you walk through the darkest valley, you will fear no evil, for your Father is with you; His rod and His staff comfort you.`, note: `You've walked through valleys most never see — and through every one, your Father walked beside you.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:6-7`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything, by prayer, bring your requests to your Father — and His peace, beyond all understanding, will guard your heart and mind.`, note: `You don't have to stand watch over the anxiety alone — hand it to your Father and let His peace take the guard.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 43:1`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 43, text: `Fear not, for I have redeemed you; I have called you by name — you are Mine, says your Father.`, note: `You are not a service number or a forgotten name to Him. He calls you by name, and He calls you His own.` },
		{ ref: `John 14:27`, slug: `john`, ch: 14, text: `Peace I leave with you; My peace I give to you. Not as the world gives do I give to you. Do not let your heart be troubled, and do not be afraid.`, note: `The peace your Father gives isn't the fragile quiet of the world — it can steady even a heart that's seen too much.` },
	]}
	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers you`}
	offersIntroHtml={`The world asks you to prove you're fine and carry it alone. Here's what your Father gives you instead — for free, because you're already His.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `A presence that never leaves`, bodyHtml: `Your Father <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/deuteronomy/31" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">will never leave you nor forsake you</a> — not on the worst night, not in the hardest transition. He was there the whole time, and He's here now.` },
		{ heading: `Healing for the wounds no one sees`, bodyHtml: `Your Father <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/147" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds</a> — including the invisible ones you carry home and don't talk about.` },
		{ heading: `Peace that can steady your heart`, bodyHtml: `You don't have to white-knuckle it alone: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/philippians/4" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">hand your worries to your Father</a>, and His peace — the kind the world can't give — stands guard over your heart and mind.` },
		{ heading: `A name beyond the uniform`, bodyHtml: `He has <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/43" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">called you by name</a> — you are His. Your identity was never your rank or your role; it's that you belong to a Father who will never let you go.` },
	]}
	whyHeading={`Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for veterans`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet God as a Father, not a distant commander`, bodyHtml: `It's easy to picture God as a far-off authority handing down orders. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1</a> on. So instead of one more chain of command, you meet the One who stood with you the whole time and welcomes you home.` },
		{ heading: `It's free, on your phone, with audio`, bodyHtml: `No account, no purchase, no app. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Read it free online</a> with audio on every chapter — listen on a drive, during a sleepless night, or before a hard appointment. The Father's voice fits right into your real day.` },
		{ heading: `It speaks to the wounds you carry`, bodyHtml: `Grief? Anxiety? The struggle to find purpose again? Start with our <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a> or learn to talk to Him with our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> — the Word meets you right where you are.` },
	]}
	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`You served, you sacrificed, you carry what most will never see — and you were never meant to carry it alone. The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; George MacDonald, Charles Spurgeon, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel different the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a quick fix — it's a foundation, and foundations get rebuilt quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that the hardest deployment couldn't, and the hardest homecoming can't, uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I saw every day of it. Every deployment, every loss, every hour you stood watch while others slept — I was there, and I never once looked away. And I want you to hear Me over the noise you carry home: you are Mine, and I love you right now — not the soldier you were, not the version that has it together. You.</p><p>You were trained to carry it alone, but you were never meant to. The wounds no one sees, I see. The grief you don't speak, I know. Come home to Me — I'll bind up what's broken and give you a name that no discharge, no failure, and no forgotten homecoming can ever take. You don't have to stand watch over your own heart anymore. I'm your Father, you were never forgotten, and I am not letting you go."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for veterans`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these veterans — for every man and woman who served, who sacrificed, who carries what most will never see. Let them hear Your whisper above the noise they carry home — the sleepless nights, the grief, the lie that they were forgotten or must carry it alone. Let them encounter Your love — not as a distant commander, but as a Father who never left their side — and know they are Yours, beyond the uniform, beyond the rank, beyond the mission.</p><p>Father, bring healing to the wounds no one can see. Bind up the brokenhearted, quiet the troubled mind, and lift the weight of survivor's guilt and moral injury that no one was built to carry. Give them honor where the world gave them silence, purpose where service left an empty place, and brothers and sisters who point them to You. I pray Your protection over them and over their families — over their marriages, their children, and their homes — and Your shield against despair, isolation, and the enemy's lies.</p><p>Let them know there is no shame in You, that they are fearfully and faithfully held, and that nothing they have seen or done can separate them from Your love. Let them know You, their Father, as their true home and their lasting reward. And may every one of them wake up knowing they were never forgotten and are deeply loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
